Reasoning: The paper deals with the interpolation of point sets in the plane using monotone functions, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The computational complexity of deciding 3-monotone interpolability is also investigated, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions a Ramsey-type result, which is a topic in combinatorics and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of semidefinite programming in the decision problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of scientific computing (cs.SC).
